40|$|AbstractThis paper {{deals with}} the modern trends in <b>typhlotechnics</b> in terms of {{quality of life for}} persons with visual {{impairment}}. A person with visual impairment is strongly influenced by the development of modern technologies. From the perspective of special education the support of people with visual impairment should take place not only by using the <b>typhlotechnics,</b> artificially made aids, but activity of the individual is equally important. The main method for the outputs of our paper selected was the analysis of foreign and local literature, mostly from the years 2008 - 2014. Comparison of specialized material allows the evaluation of the current state of development in the area and creation of an informational base for further research projects...|$|E

